description:
The tail command fails with:
```
Error: get player: no player configured - run 'riff auth' first
```

Even when the user is authenticated with Spotify.

Root cause: The `getPlayer()` function in `internal/cli/tail.go` is a placeholder that always returns an error:

```go
func getPlayer() (core.Player, error) {
    // TODO: Get player from config/discovery
    return nil, fmt.Errorf("no player configured - run 'riff auth' first")
}
```

Fix: Implement proper player initialization using the Spotify client, similar to how other commands (play, status, etc.) get their player.
